		<!-- Begin Comments -->
		
		<b>Comment By mbartley, 3-25-09</b>
		<p>I can't tell you how happy I am to have another Carlson novel. As a long time traveler in and around the Winds, I am excited to read his take on that magnificent range. Five Skies was a beautiful story about men and work and the land. I discovered him through your work here at New West along with Deirdre McNamer's Red Rover. I can't thank you enough for bringing these wonderful storytellers and their stories into my life. Finally, I've just recently finished Killing for Coal and am looking forward to your opinion. Congratulations to Professor Andrews for a well deserved honor.</p>
		
